In some species such as
T. zebra
, the presence of a pharyngeal tooth seems to be size-dependent, as mid-sized and large specimens lack one ( San Martín 1984 , 2003;
San Martín et al 2008
). Nonetheless, in
T. microdenticulata
n. sp.
the pharyngeal tooth is always present, while the only size-related differences is trepan teeth. The trepan is a diagnostic character of the genus (San Martín 2003 ), and it is considered homoplasic, so that it should be used with care to differentiate lower taxa (
Aguado & San Martín 2009
).
